    "course_title": "APPLIED DATABASE DESIGN",
    "description": "Introduces the applications of databases to real-world data and information problems.  Overview of the principles and practices of user-oriented database design, management, and application. Discussion and practice cover database application lifecycle, data modeling, relational database design, SQL queries, reports and other interfaces to database data, and database documentation.",
